In this statement, the President strongly condemns the attack on the diplomatic facility in Benghazi, which resulted in the deaths of four Americans, including Ambassador Chris Stevens. He expresses his condolences to the families of the victims and praises their commitment to freedom, justice, and partnership with other nations. The President directs his Administration to provide necessary resources to support the security of personnel in Libya and increase security at diplomatic posts worldwide. He emphasizes the rejection of efforts to denigrate religious beliefs while unequivocally opposing senseless violence. The President personally acknowledges Ambassador Stevens' bravery and service to the United States, highlighting his support for Libya's transition to democracy. He recognizes the service and sacrifices made by American civilians globally and calls for redoubled efforts to continue their work.